sheetydrums — third-party components, credits, and licensing
============================================================

The source code in this repository is licensed under the MIT License (see
LICENSE). However, the project relies on pretrained model weights that are
downloaded at runtime and carry their own licenses. Two of them are
NonCommercial, which makes the project **as a whole non-commercial**:

Model weights
-------------
- ADTOF (drum transcription) — Zehren et al., Signals 2023.
  Weights: CC-BY-NC-SA 4.0 (NonCommercial, ShareAlike, Attribution).
  https://github.com/MZehren/ADTOF  (PyTorch port: adtof-pytorch)

- DrumSep MDX23C (drum sub-stem separation) — jarredou / aufr33.
  Weights: CC-BY-NC-SA 4.0 (NonCommercial, ShareAlike, Attribution).
  Loaded via `audio-separator`.

- Demucs v4 / htdemucs_ft (stem separation) — Meta AI. MIT.
  https://github.com/facebookresearch/demucs

- Beat This! (beat + downbeat tracking) — Foscarin, Schlüter, Widmer,
  ISMIR 2024. MIT.  https://github.com/CPJKU/beat_this

The two CC-BY-NC-SA weights are **not redistributed** in this repository;
they are downloaded from their original sources on first run.

Method credit
-------------
- The 5-class → richer-vocabulary expansion (open/closed hi-hat, ride/crash,
  tom pitch) follows Cheuk et al., "Enhanced ADT via Drum Stem Source
  Separation," arXiv:2509.24853 (ISMIR 2024 LBD).

Libraries
---------
- VexFlow (music notation rendering) — MIT.
- yt-dlp (audio fetching) — Unlicense / public domain.

Practical summary
-----------------
Because ADTOF and DrumSep ship NonCommercial weights, do not use this project
commercially. Attribute the above when redistributing. See docs/v2-backlog.md
("Robustness & licensing") for the path to a commercially-clean pipeline.
